description:
Create a mutation for modifying the list that an issue belongs to in a board - we need to copy the REST API behaviour.

REST request (for a project board):

```
PUT /-/boards/2/issues/3

{from_list_id: 6, to_list_id: 7, move_before_id: 2, move_after_id: 1}
```

The GraphQL might look like (but using global IDs instead of integer values):

```graphql
mutation {
  issueMoveList(input: { projectPath: "group/project", iid: "3", from: "6", to: "7", move_before: "2", move_after: "1"}) {
    errors
  }
}
```

Part of board refactoring. Allow reordering of lists within GraphQL.

REST query:

```
PUT /-/boards/4/lists/15

list: {position: 2, collapsed: false}
```

The equivalent GraphQL would be something like

```graphql
mutation {
  updateList(input: { list: "gid://gitlab/List/15", position: 2, collapsed: false }) {
    errors
  }
}
```

### Problem to solve

In order to send vulnerability tracking events for [https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/issues/229617](https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/issues/229617), we need to create a [self describing JSON schema](https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/iglu/-/tree/master/public/schemas/com.gitlab) to provide details of the given tracking event.

### Proposal

1. [x] Create a new self describing JSON schema in the [iglu repository](https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/iglu). This JSON schema should be generic so that it can be used for _all secure products_:

   ```json
